---
description: Apply pytest 8.x testing patterns. Use when writing or modifying tests.
globs: tests/**/*.py, tests/**/*.yaml
alwaysApply: false
---

Test Structure:
- Unit tests: `tests/<module>/test_*.py`
- Action tests: `tests/actions/<action>/test_*.yaml` (YAML-driven)
- Test data: `tests/<module>/test_data/`

Patterns:
- AAA: Arrange, Act, Assert
- Use `pytest.fixture` for shared setup
- Use `@pytest.mark.parametrize` for data-driven tests
- Use `tmp_path` fixture for filesystem tests

YAML Test Format (for actions):
- `cli_arguments.options` — CLI flags to pass
- `checks` — list of assertions (`exist`, `contains`, `not_exist`, `not_contains`)

Markers:
- `@pytest.mark.unit` — fast unit tests
- `@pytest.mark.integration` — slower integration tests
- `@pytest.mark.slow` — very slow tests

Running:
- All: `uv run pytest`
- Specific: `uv run pytest tests/actions/ --action-filter="core" -v`
- Coverage: `uv run pytest --cov=septeo_scaffolder --cov-report=term-missing`

Avoid:
- Tests without assertions
- Mocking internal modules — mock at boundaries only
- Test interdependencies — each test must be independent
